Ad Text:
One of Australia's biggest tech environments is finally doing what so many only talk about: putting AI at the heart of the business.

This isn't just about chatbots or proof-of-concepts. This is enterprise-level AI transformation across customer, network, fraud, operations, and beyond. And they're not looking for someone to follow the roadmap - they're looking for someone to write it.

If you've been stuck on the sidelines, watching organisations play it safe, now's your chance to get on the pitch and architect something that actually matters.




What you'll be doing:
Define and own the AI architecture strategy across a multi-billion dollar organisation.
Lead the design of scalable, production-ready AI/ML solutions across multiple domains (yes, including GenAI - but not only GenAI).
Partner with product, data, and engineering leaders to make things happen. No siloes. No lip service.
Embed responsible AI frameworks - because scale without governance isn't innovation, it's a time bomb.
Be the voice that translates technical complexity into boardroom clarity.


What you bring:
A track record of building real-world AI systems - not just lab experiments or vendor demos.
Deep knowledge across ML ops, model lifecycle, cloud platforms (GCP/AWS/Azure), and LLMs.
Gravitas. You can hold your own with engineers and executives - and know when to challenge both.
Telco experience? Great. But if you've worked in any complex, regulated, data-heavy environment, you'll fit right in.

What's in it for you:
A seat at the table. This team has top-down backing and budget to build properly.
A chance to shape AI capability from the ground up
Flexible work, strong package, and a leadership team that actually gets it.


If you're tired of spinning your wheels, this is your chance to do something that moves the needle.

Perth, WA

Brisbane, QLD

Are you ready to lead cutting-edge projects and shape the future of industrial process solutions?¬†

Honeywell is seeking a Senior Advanced Process Simulation Engineer with deep expertise in Process Simulation and Operator Training Simulator (OTS) solutions. This is a pivotal role where you will deliver advanced solutions, mentor talented engineers, and engage with top-tier clients across the Pacific region.

Why You‚Äôll Love This Role

Be the Subject Matter Expert (SME) driving innovation in process simulation and OTS.

Work on high-impact projects for major clients in LNG, Petrochemical, and MMM sectors.

Collaborate with industry leaders and influence strategic business outcomes.

Enjoy a culture that values technical excellence, client success, and continuous learning.

Key Responsibilities

Lead and deliver OTS and Process Simulation projects for major clients.

Provide technical consultation and mentoring to intermediate and graduate engineers.

Collaborate with Project Managers, Sales, and Consulting teams for business development and technical support.

Ensure high-quality proposals, accurate estimations, and on-time delivery.

Build and maintain strong client relationships to drive satisfaction and repeat business.

Must-Have Skills & Experience

15+ years of experience in Process Simulation and relevant industry experience.

Proven expertise in OTS implementation and integration.

Strong process and operations knowledge of LNG, Petrochemical, and MMM verticals.

Hands-on experience with DCS integration and safety systems of various makes.

Ability to troubleshoot and work independently with customers and EPCMs.

Proven experience in Process Design and optimisation studies using simulation tools.

Excellent communication and technical writing skills.

Highly Desirable

Experience with cloud-based deployment architectures (Azure, AWS).

Knowledge of simulation-based real-time Digital Twins.

Familiarity with real-time optimisation applications and integration with advanced process control.

Prior involvement in sales support and proposal development.

What We Offer

Competitive compensation and benefits.

Opportunities for career growth and global exposure.

A collaborative environment where innovation thrives.

The Future Is What We Make It at Honeywell. Company description:



We are a joint venture between Tianqi Lithium Corporation and IGO Ltd. As pioneers in the Australian lithium industry, we've already achieved great things, including building the first battery-grade lithium hydroxide plant in Australia, paving the way for Australia to be a major player in the global transition to a clean energy future.

We're looking for people who want to be a part of the industry of the future - people who work with purpose and urgency, take initiative, and rise to challenges. We're seeking individuals who empower others, embrace innovation, and want to work in an open and supportive environment, where teamwork and collaboration are valued.

At TLEA, you'll be part of a team that is excited to be involved in a world-class project that benefits not only the Western Australian community but the world.



Job description:

Are you passionate about creating real impact through engineering excellence?


TLEA is currently inviting applications for a full-time Process Control Systems Engineer to join our team at the Kwinana refinery within our Operations. This role operates on a Monday to Friday roster and offers the opportunity to contribute meaningfully to a dynamic and innovative workplace.
As the successful candidate, you will be responsible for the development, maintenance, and optimisation of instrumentation and control systems across our plant. Your work will be critical in ensuring operational efficiency and reliability.


We're looking for someone who embodies our core values of distinction, pragmatism, honesty, tenacity, and innovation. This role is ideal for a technically minded, approachable, and action-oriented individual who thrives on problem-solving, meets tight deadlines with confidence, and maintains a strong focus on delivering solutions.



Profile description:


Design and improve on engineering solutions to optimise performance, prevent operational & production delays, and minimise lifecycle costs of the Process Control System, instrumentation, and related infrastructure.
Review and improve process control strategies.
PID tuning.
Alarm rationalisation.
Updating and testing of control system software, firmware, and patches.
Reporting.
Configure and maintain the Process Control System, instrumentation, and related infrastructure.
Implement changes according to the Management of Change processes.
Configure and commission VSDs, DOLs, Network switches, instrumentation, and other related equipment.
Analyse assets (PCS components) and predict maintenance requirements.
Identify and assess risks using enterprise risk framework policies and procedures, develop and implement risk mitigation plans.
Assist in fault finding and failure investigations, and the subsequent rectification work.
Stay up to date on control system developments.
Assist in developing electrical technicians within the control and instrumentation environment.

About you

Tertiary Engineering degree with professional experience in process control and instrumentation
Good understanding of distributed control systems and control system architectures
Extensive experience with PLC & SCADA programming (AB Studio 5000, AB FTView SE)
Demonstrated ability to understand control philosophies and configuring the control system as per the functional requirements
PID loop tuning on complex systems.
Configuration and commissioning of field instrumentation and equipment (eg VSDs, DOLs, switches)
Excellent problem solving and fault-finding skills
Good understanding of Industrial protocols
Excellent communication skills
Highly adept at MS Office suite (especially Excel)
Previous experience in chemical or mineral processing industry
Rockwell PlantPAx DCS
Configuring and commissioning of Powerflex drives, E300 DOLs & Stratix switches
Siemens TIA
Robots (ABB, Kawasaki)
Historians (FTHistorian, Influx, Osisoft Pi)
Experience programming in VBA or similar
Networking, virtualisation, and server management
Communication protocols Modbus TCP, Modbus RTU, and EthernetIP, OPC
Cybersecurity exposure
Functional Safety
PowerBI



We offer:


Contribute to a green and sustainable industry of the future.
Competitive salary with a performance-based discretionary bonus structure
Additional Superannuation
Rewards and recognition program
Long service leave option after 5 years (pro rata)
Supportive colleagues committed to your success and well-being
Inclusive and diverse work environment

About us: At Fast Automation ‚ÄúCulture is everything‚Äù we have worked hard to create a great culture and are a tight knit & highly driven group, with constant engagement and a rapid learning and development focus. Aside from that, we have performed over 1800 projects without ever failing, many of these were difficult world firsts! We are also playing with some exciting emerging technologies (Robotics and vision based products). So come and have some challenging fun while moving forward quickly in your career by benefiting from being alongside some of the best engineers in the business.

Fast Automation are looking for experienced Automation Project Engineers to add to our team to help deliver new projects mainly around the Sydney & Melbourne area. The role will involve Leading electrical design, PLC/HMI/SCADA/ROBOTICS and more development, FAT testing, site commissioning and SAT testing to deliver automation solutions to our clients. You will be largely autonomous, a self starter and capable of working in a team or alone on smaller projects. The position is based in Macquarie Park, NSW and Onsite with occasional travel to various locations around Australia.

5 plus years in integrating projects using Automation technology is a necessity for this role, but please do enquire if you wish to be considered into the future. The ability to quickly get up to speed on requirements, comprehend technical information, design, read electrical schematics and code, design safety circuits & commissioning experience are expected. We are looking for an intelligent engineer who is self driven, disciplined, ¬†well organised, a fast learner with personality and naturally interested in Robotics, PLCs, HMIs, and SCADA control systems.

Ideally you will be experienced with:

¬∑¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Robots

¬∑¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† PLC's (Ideally Siemens and Rockwell)

¬∑¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† SCADA Systems

¬∑¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Electrical design & commissioning

Agents please do not enquire.

Please note, due to the high volume of applications received, only short listed candidates will be contacted.

‚Ä¢Are you eligible to work in Australia?
‚Ä¢How many years experience do you have in a similar role?

Job Title: Robotics Engineer (12 Month Fixed Term Contract)
Ad Text:
As peAbout Us

Konica Minolta is innovative, robust and continually evolving. From printing, scanning and copying to cloud storage and robotics, our award-winning products and solutions help companies to transform and move information faster. Our people make this possible and as an organisation, we offer workplace flexibility, support diversity and promote events and activities to support wellbeing. We strive to create and maintain an inclusive workforce as diverse and capable as our class-leading solutions. We actively encourage women and those from diverse backgrounds to apply for our roles.

¬†

About the role

We're seeking a Robotics Engineer who is both a skilled technical professional and a great communicator. This dynamic role is a unique mix of internal technical work and direct customer interaction. You'll use your expertise in Industrial Automation and Industry 4.0 technologies to support the entire customer journey‚Äîfrom pre-sales demonstrations and on-site deployments to proof of concepts and post-sales support. If you're a hands-on problem-solver who enjoys working directly with customers to see a project through to success, this is the perfect opportunity. This role is a 12-month fixed term contract.


Key responsibilities

Understand Konica Minolta‚Äôs robotics offering and be able to simply and effectively communicate its capabilities to internal and external customers.

Act as a technical point of contact for customers, assisting with pre-sales activities, solution development, and product demonstrations.

Support Sales team members with required technical information solutioning needs.

Create simulations and conduct Proof of Concepts (PoCs) to validate technical solutions and showcase the value of the robotics platform in customer-specific environments.

Travel to customer sites for on-site deployments, system commissioning, and providing hands-on technical support.

Provide timely and effective post-sales support, troubleshooting issues, and maintaining strong relationships with existing clients to ensure their long-term satisfaction.

Integrate robotics hardware and software into client environments with involvement of our partner or third-party provider, if required.

Contribute to the creation and maintenance of technical documentation, including system specifications, user manuals, and deployment guides.

Stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in Industrial Automation and Industry 4.0 technologies to continuously improve solution offerings.




Who are we looking for?

A Bachelor's degree in Robotics, Mechatronics, Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or a related technical field.

Demonstrated experience in Industrial automation, Mobile robotics, or related technical field

Hands-on Technical Expertise: Proven experience with industrial automation components, PLCs, sensors, and robotics systems.

Programming Proficiency: Strong programming skills in languages like C++, Python, or ROS (Robot Operating System).

Troubleshooting & Problem-Solving: Excellent diagnostic skills for both hardware and software issues.

Customer-Facing Abilities: Strong communication and interpersonal skills to effectively engage with clients during pre-sales, deployment, and post-sales support.

Project Lifecycle Knowledge: Experience supporting projects through various stages, from proof of concept to full-scale deployment. Konica Minolta compliance procedures, the successful candidate will be required to undertake background checks.


Benefits

What can KM offer you?
We‚Äôre proud to be Certified‚Ñ¢ by Great Place To Work¬Æ, reflecting the commitment we make to building a positive, inclusive and empowering culture. At Konica Minolta you will enjoy a collaborative team culture where you will be supported and empowered to contribute your ideas and identify opportunities to develop your team and yourself. We are dedicated to the values of diversity and inclusion and have a firm commitment to ethical practices and corporate responsibility.

Konica Minolta is committed to providing a working environment that is inclusive and fair to both women and men. Progressive policies such as our domestic violence policy; paid parental leave and flexible workplace policies enable our people to balance work and life responsibilities.


Equal Opportunities
We are committed to providing equal opportunities and actively encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply for our roles, regardless of gender, age, sexual orientation, ethnicity, religion or disability.
If you require any adjustments/assistance during the recruitment process, please reach out to careers@konicaminolta.com.au


Join our Team¬†and thrive in an¬†environment¬†built on strong¬†Collaboration,¬†continuous¬†Learning¬†and personal¬†Growth.¬†Everyday¬†at Konica Minolta is an¬†opportunity¬†to¬†share¬†your¬†Ideas, influence¬†Change¬†and engage with colleagues from¬†diverse backgrounds and¬†experiences.

Leading Financial Services Company
Implement full-stack visibility across infrastructure/applications
Our client is a leading, enterprise Fin-Services organisation with a strong focus on innovation, reliability, and operational excellence across its technology landscape.

Role Overview

As an Observability Engineer, you will:

Support and maintain an enterprise-grade observability platform built on the Elastic Stack.
Implement end-to-end visibility across infrastructure and applications to enable proactive monitoring and performance insights.
Drive anomaly detection and root cause analysis to ensure operational excellence and business continuity.
Integrate logs, metrics, traces, and synthetics into a unified observability pipeline.
Develop and maintain Kibana dashboards, visualisations and alerting mechanisms aligned with SLIs and SLOs.
Implement machine learning models for anomaly detection and predictive analytics.
Optimise data ingestion, transformation, and storage to enhance performance and scalability.
Skills & Experience

5+ years‚Äô experience working with the Elastic Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana, Beats, APM).
Strong understanding of observability concepts ‚Äì logs, metrics, traces, SLIs/SLOs.
Proven experience with data ingestion pipelines, parsing, enrichment, and indexing.
Knowledge of machine learning and anomaly detection strategies.
Desirable:

Experience with OpenTelemetry (OTEL).
Knowledge of ITIL practices.
Exposure to CI/CD automation and infrastructure as code.
Familiarity with containerised environments (Docker, Kubernetes).
What‚Äôs on Offer

Opportunity to work within a large-scale enterprise technology environment focused on innovation and reliability.
Join a high-performing Cloud and Infrastructure team working on next-generation observability solutions.
Collaborative culture that values technical excellence and continuous improvement.
How to Apply
If you have strong experience in observability engineering, automation, and cloud infrastructure and are passionate about building systems that enhance reliability and insight, please click apply now.

Ad Text:
Applications close at 11:30 pm AEDT Thursday 20th November 2025 (late applications will not be accepted).

The Australian Sports Commission is embarking on the Green and Gold decade. An exciting time filled with international sporting competitions on home soil, including the Men‚Äôs and Women‚Äôs Rugby World Cup, and culminating in the Brisbane 2032 Olympic and Paralympic Games. We have an ambitious new Strategic Vision and we need the best players on our team to help us deliver real results for the sporting sector and all Australians.

Are you up for the challenge?

About the team ‚Äì The Sport Intelligence & Analytics team leverages data to enhance athlete performance and deliver a competitive advantage to Australia‚Äôs high-performance system. The team delivers data engineering, data analytics, data science and data governance support and leads the administration of the Athlete Management System and AIS Hub digital platform for the Australian high-performance system.¬†

About the role ‚Äì The Senior Data Engineer role will be responsible for architecture and operation of national high-performance sport data systems that turn raw performance signals into decisions for coaches and athletes. Lead the design, operation, and continuous improvement of secure, scalable data platforms (Snowflake, AWS, Dagster/dbt) for the AIS and broader Australian high-performance network. Work autonomously in a small team, collaborate widely, and model high standards in delivery, governance, and coaching.

About you ‚Äì We are looking for an analytical individual with excellent attention to detail, experienced learning new systems and tasks and is adaptive and responsive to changing circumstances.¬†
The successful candidate will have:
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Extensive experience in Python and SQL.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Experience building and optimising data pipelines, architectures and datasets.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Experience in small cross-functional teams in a dynamic environment.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Strong analytics skills related to working with unstructured datasets.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Experience working with and managing data engineering tools such as Dagster, Airflow, DBT, Snowflake and ETL/ELT software.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Experience across emerging data engineering and database technologies.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Experience working with CI/CD tools such as Gitlab, Azure Devops.
‚Ä¢ ¬† ¬†Experience with cloud infrastructure (at least one major cloud, Azure, AWS or GCP), i.e. container orchestration basics, IAM, networking, and cost-aware design.

This position is offered as an ONGOING.

Why work with us?
We have offices located in Canberra, Melbourne and Sydney. ¬†Across all locations, we offer:

Options for flexible working arrangements.
Annual allowances towards training based on individualised career goals.
Access to a customised ASC L&D calendar for ongoing professional and career development.
Generous superannuation scheme with up to 15.4% employer contributions.
Corporate discount on AIS Shop merchandise.
Access to Clearinghouse for Sport, an information sharing platform for Sporting professionals.

Additionally, our Canberra campus offers:

Free onsite parking
Onsite facilities including caf√©, dining hall, gym, and swimming pool.
Priority placement for your children to access the award winning, onsite AIS Caretaker‚Äôs Cottage Childcare Centre.

If you have any questions about this opportunity, please contact:

Contact Office: Xin Cai
Email address: xin.cai@ausport.gov.au¬†

Acknowledgement of Country ¬†
The Australian Sports Commission (ASC) acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of the lands where its offices are located, the Ngunnawal people and recognises any other people or families with connection to the lands of the ACT and region, the Wurundjeri Woi-wurrung people of the Kulin Nation, the people of the Yugambeh Nation and the Gadigal people of the Eora Nation. The ASC extends this acknowledgment to all the Traditional Custodians of the lands and First Nations peoples throughout Australia and would like to pay respects to all Elders past and present. The ASC recognises the outstanding contribution that Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples make to society and sport in Australia and celebrates the power of sport to promote reconciliation and reduce inequality.¬†

Job Title: Research Scientist, Vision Language and Multimodal Modeling
Ad Text:
At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google‚Äôs technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.

Minimum qualifications:

PhD degree in Computer Science, a related field, or equivalent practical experience.
One or more scientific publication submissions for conferences, journals, or public repositories (such as CVPR, ICCV, NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR, etc.).
Preferred qualifications:

Experience in areas like face anti-spoofing, biometrics, 3D/2.5D vision, facial landmark/pose estimation.
Experience with TensorFlow, Flume, common computer vision libraries/frameworks and Android.

Interest to build production systems.

Excellent software engineering skills (e.g., C++, python, data processing, production backend development, etc.).
About the job


As an organization, Google maintains a portfolio of research projects driven by fundamental research, new product innovation, product contribution and infrastructure goals, while providing individuals and teams the freedom to emphasize specific types of work. As a Research Scientist, you'll setup large-scale tests and deploy promising ideas quickly and broadly, managing deadlines and deliverables while applying the latest theories to develop new and improved products, processes, or technologies. From creating experiments and prototyping implementations to designing new architectures, our research scientists work on real-world problems that span the breadth of computer science, such as machine (and deep) learning, data mining, natural language processing, hardware and software performance analysis, improving compilers for mobile platforms, as well as core search and much more.

As a Research Scientist, you'll also actively contribute to the wider research community by sharing and publishing your findings, with ideas inspired by internal projects as well as from collaborations with research programs at partner universities and technical institutes all over the world.

In this role, you will develop models and architectures grounded in foundation models, data-efficient algorithms, and federated learning.

Responsibilities

Author research papers to share and generate impact of research results across the team and in the research community.

Help in growing research business across teams by sharing research trends and best practices within the community.

Define the data structure, framework, design, and evaluation metrics for research solution development and implementation under minimal guidance. Identify timelines and obtain resources needed.

Identify new and upcoming research areas by interacting with external and internal collaborators. Help in developing research strategy and plans to expand the impact of Google research with some guidance.
Contribute to conducting experiments based on the research question. Develop research prototypes or conduct simulations to further evaluate the impact of research, finalize hypotheses, and refine the research methodology under minimal guidance.
